possible MFS treatment strategy, but interactions with TGF-β signaling remain 
elusive. Heterozygous loss-of-function mutations in TGF-β receptors 1 and 2 
(TGFBR1 and TGFBR2) cause LDS, but TGF-β signaling is activated in the aorta 
(referred to as the TGF-β paradox) by mechanisms yet to be elucidated. In this 
review, we present and discuss the current understanding of molecular mechanisms 
responsible for aortopathies of MFS and related disorders.

